# HRMS Design System

All UI work MUST use the shared design system. Do not invent one-off card, toolbar, empty, or error patterns.

## Class tokens

Import from `@/lib/ui/design-system`:

| Token | Use for |
|-------|---------|
| `uiCard` | Static cards |
| `uiCardInteractive` | Clickable/hoverable cards |
| `uiDialog` | Modal panels |
| `uiInput` / `uiSelect` | Form fields |
| `uiPrimaryBtn` | Primary CTAs (prefer `PrimaryButton`) |
| `uiOutlineBtn` | Secondary/outline actions |
| `uiSkeletonBlock` | Skeleton backgrounds |
| `uiEmptyStateShell` / `uiEmptyStateIconRing` | Empty states (prefer `CommonEmptyState`) |
| `uiErrorBanner` | Inline errors (prefer `CommonErrorBanner`) |
| `statusBadgeClasses` | Status pills (prefer `CommonStatusBadge`) |

## Mandatory shared components

Import from `@/components/common`:

| Component | Use instead of |
|-----------|----------------|
| `CommonPageHeader` | Raw `<h1>` + subtitle blocks |
| `CommonStatCards` | Inline stat count grids |
| `CommonListToolbar` | Custom search + filter rows |
| `CommonFilterChips` | Inline tab/chip filter buttons |
| `CommonEmptyState` | Custom empty-state divs |
| `CommonErrorBanner` | Red inline alert divs |
| `CommonErrorState` | Full-page error panels |
| `CommonPageSkeleton` | Ad-hoc Suspense skeletons |
| `CommonStatusBadge` | Inline status span styling |
| `CommonFormFieldError` | Raw field error `<p>` tags |
| `CommonCard` | Repeated card wrappers |

## Buttons

- Primary actions: `PrimaryButton` from `@/components/ui/primary-button`
- Other variants: shadcn `Button` with `uiOutlineBtn` or design tokens

| `uiTableShell` | Desktop table wrapper |
| `uiSectionHeader` | Section h2 + subtitle + border |
| `uiTabChipBase` / `uiTabChipActive` / `uiTabChipInactive` | Settings/top tab chips |
| `getEmployeeStatusBadgeVariant()` | Map employee status strings to badge variants |

## Additional shared components

| Component | Use instead of |
|-----------|----------------|
| `CommonStatCardDisplay` | Non-clickable KPI cards (%, currency) |
| `CommonPagination` | Custom prev/next page controls |
| `CommonMobileCardGrid` | `lg:hidden` card grid shell |

## Settings shared primitives

Import from `@/components/settings/shared`:

| Component | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `SettingsMasterCard` | Master list shells (title, Add, rows, empty) |
| `SettingsFormDialog` | Add/edit dialogs with `uiDialog` footer |
| `SettingsDeleteDialog` | Standardized delete confirmations |
| `SettingsListRow` | Rows with mobile-visible action buttons |

## Standard page file layout

```
feature/
├── feature-list.tsx          # composition root
├── feature-page-header.tsx
├── feature-stats-cards.tsx   # optional
├── feature-toolbar.tsx
├── feature-card.tsx          # mobile
├── feature-card-skeleton.tsx
└── feature-table.tsx         # desktop optional
```

## Reference implementations

- Requests list: `components/requests/requests-list.tsx`
- Documents grid: `components/documents/documents-grid.tsx`
- Assets list: `components/assets/assets-list.tsx`
- Employees list: `components/employees/employees-list.tsx`
- Settings panel: `components/settings/settings-panel.tsx`
- New request page: `components/requests/create-request-page.tsx`

## Rules

1. Never hardcode `rounded-md` on new UI — use `rounded-xl` (controls) or `rounded-2xl` (cards/dialogs).
2. Never duplicate empty/error/toolbar markup — extend `components/common/` if a pattern is missing.
3. Skeletons use `uiSkeletonBlock` (`bg-midnight/60`), not arbitrary gray classes.
4. Page Suspense fallbacks use `CommonPageSkeleton`.
5. See also: `front-end-cursor-rules.mdc`, `ultimate-frontend-development-guide.mdc`.
